          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Angular anisotropy of the fragments from fission",
                "of Th-232 and Pu-238 by 13.40 - 14.80 MeV neutrons"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "      Deuteron-tritium reaction",
                " Deuterons energy 0.2 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "           Direct detection"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GLASD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "    Glass detector for FF",
                "Multi-angle detector for neutron energy measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The quantity of angular anisotropy is defined according",
                "to the statistical model of the nuclear fission."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LEAST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Angular anisotropy is found from the Least-",
                " Squares fit to measurements at various angles",
                " according to the formula",
                "           W(phi)/W(90.deg.)=1+A*COS(phi)**2,",
                " where \"phi\" is angle between neutron direction and",
                " the fragment direction"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- For Pu-238 the results of two independent pairs",
                "of measurements are presented thus demonstrating",
                "their accuracy.",
                "- Of compiler M.M.",
                "Data are given in YFI-13, but no explanation of",
                "anisotropy in YFI-13. In JEL,15,228,1972 the angular",
                "anisotropy is defined as A=W(0deg)/W(90deg)-1 in",
                "text, page 228, but as W(0deg)/W(90deg) in title of",
                "figure ; as supposed, a misprint in title of figure,",
                "because data are compared with 13708.004 -e.g. 1.40 at",
                "14.1 MeV. So, values given in table 1 are the angular",
                "anisotropy A=W(90deg)/W(90deg)-1."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " All errors are statistical"
